*mb_strwidth*

(PHP 4 >= 4.0.6, PHP 5, PHP 7)

mb_strwidth â€” Return width of string

===============================================================================
[ Description ]

  mb_strwidth ( string $str [, string $encoding = mb_internal_encoding() ] ) :~
  int~

Returns the width of string {str}, where halfwidth characters count as 1, and
fullwidth characters count as 2.

The fullwidth characters are: U+1100-U+115F, U+11A3-U+11A7, U+11FA-U+11FF,
U+2329-U+232A, U+2E80-U+2E99, U+2E9B-U+2EF3, U+2F00-U+2FD5, U+2FF0-U+2FFB,
U+3000-U+303E, U+3041-U+3096, U+3099-U+30FF, U+3105-U+312D, U+3131-U+318E,
U+3190-U+31BA, U+31C0-U+31E3, U+31F0-U+321E, U+3220-U+3247, U+3250-U+32FE,
U+3300-U+4DBF, U+4E00-U+A48C, U+A490-U+A4C6, U+A960-U+A97C, U+AC00-U+D7A3,
U+D7B0-U+D7C6, U+D7CB-U+D7FB, U+F900-U+FAFF, U+FE10-U+FE19, U+FE30-U+FE52,
U+FE54-U+FE66, U+FE68-U+FE6B, U+FF01-U+FF60, U+FFE0-U+FFE6, U+1B000-U+1B001,
U+1F200-U+1F202, U+1F210-U+1F23A, U+1F240-U+1F248, U+1F250-U+1F251, U+20000-
U+2FFFD, U+30000-U+3FFFD. All other characters are halfwidth characters.

===============================================================================
[ Parameters ]

{str}

  The string being decoded.

{encoding}

  The {encoding} parameter is the character encoding. If it is omitted, the
  internal character encoding value will be used.

===============================================================================
[ Return Values ]

The width of string {str}.

===============================================================================
[ See Also ]

 * |mb_strimwidth| - Get truncated string with specified width
 * |mb_internal_encoding| - Set/Get internal character encoding


